Nepal Friends of the Commonwealth (UK)
This friendship Seat was dedicated on 3rd September 2000
in loving memory of the lat
LT Gareth Evans and SGT Balram Rar
of the 69th Gurkha Field Squadron
who lost their lives in service during NATO peacekeeping
operations in Kosovo on 21st June 1999"”
–In Loving Memory of JEAN KATHLEEN LEIGHTON DAVIES
30 NOV 1920 - 17 NOV 1982
Wife of JOHN, Mother of JAMES & HELEN & Grandmother
AND THOU
BESIDE ME SINGING IN THE WILDERNESS
AND WILDERNESS IS PARADISE NOW"Ÿ
÷This Seat is dedicated to GEORGE COOKE, Superintendent of the Hampton Court Gardens from 1974 to 1990.
It was his vision and inspiration that lead to the creation of this garden and the training of gardeners here."„
